Appendix A1 — Glossary
Terms specific to the roadmap. See also Ambient Turn Appendix A1 for broader terminology.

Stage — a major phase of Helm's development, defined by an outcome rather than a feature list. A stage closes when its exit outcomes are achieved.
BA (Build Area) — a scoped unit of work within a stage. Each stage has its own BA counter (Stage 1 BA1-N, Stage 2 BA1-N, etc.).
Exit Outcome — a concrete marker that closes a stage. Outcomes describe what Helm can do, not how the code looks.
Load-Bearing Assumption — an assumption the roadmap depends on that is untested or unproven. Flagged explicitly wherever it appears; consolidated in Appendix A3.
Tier (T1/T2/T3) — proactivity levels: on-demand, scheduled, ambient.
Surface — a device or environment where users engage Helm.
Feat — a discrete capability Helm invokes in specific operational contexts.
Cold Start — the onboarding flow for a new user meeting Helm for the first time.
Commodity viability proof — the bet that T2 works on user-grade hardware or cloud, making productization feasible without Thor-per-user.


